	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "kernel: Out of bounds read in inet_diag_msg_sctp{,l}addr_fill() and sctp_get_sctp_info() in SCTP stack (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2017-7558",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2017-7558",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A kernel data leak due to an out-of-bound read was found in the Linux kernel in inet_diag_msg_sctp{,l}addr_fill() and sctp_get_sctp_info() functions present since version 4.7-rc1 through version 4.13. A data leak happens when these functions fill in sockaddr data structures used to export socket's diagnostic information. As a result, up to 100 bytes of the slab data could be leaked to a userspace. \n            STATEMENT: This issue does not affect Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5 and 6 as the code with the flaw is not present in the products listed.\n\nThis issue affects Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7 and Red Hat Enterprise MRG 2. Future updates for the respective releases may address this issue.",
